HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 1156
By Hemmer
A RESOLUTION to recognize Bert Mathews upon his receipt of
the Impact Award.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should pause to
salute those citizens who, through their extraordinary efforts, have distinguished themselves as
community leaders of whom we can all be proud; and
WHEREAS, Bert Mathews is one such estimable person, who recently received the
Impact Award, a most befitting honor that recognizes his career-long dedication to and
significant influence in Tennessee's real estate industry; and
WHEREAS, the Impact Award recognizes those commercial real estate (CRE)
professionals, whose work has made a lasting impact in the industry and the community through
vision, innovation, and responsible growth, and celebrates leaders who demonstrate excellence
in real estate development, investment, brokerage, or advisory services; and
WHEREAS, recipients of the award are distinguished by their ability to influence the
community in meaningful ways by delivering projects, partnerships, and initiatives that
strengthen the local economy, enhance neighborhoods, and elevate standards across the CRE
industry; through leadership, collaboration, and a commitment to long-term value, these
professionals help define the character and trajectory of Nashville; and
WHEREAS, Bert Mathews has more than forty years of experience in commercial real
estate services and has represented his clients as a developer and broker with distinction and
professionalism; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Mathews currently serves as chief executive officer of The Mathews
Company, in which role he manages development, acquisitions, financing, institutional and
investor relations, and supervision of all real estate marketing activities; and
HJR1156
015990
- 1 -

WHEREAS, Bert Mathews also serves Colliers International Nashville as principal and
executive vice president, providing services to clients of the Nashville office; and
WHEREAS, a leader in his community and his profession, Mr. Mathews previously
served as chairman of the Nashville Chamber of Commerce, Global Governing Trustee of the
Urban Land Institute, vice chairman of the Nashville Airport Authority, and chairman of the
Metropolitan Transit Authority; he is currently a member of the ThinkTennessee board; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Mathews earned his undergraduate degree from the University of North
Carolina at Chapel Hill and graduated from Harvard Business School; and
WHEREAS, Bert Mathews's distinguished career in the commercial real estate industry
demonstrates his unwavering commitment to his community and his profession, and he is richly
deserving of our approbation; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we honor and recognize Bert Mathews on his receipt of the Impact Award,
extending to him our best wishes for much continued success in all his future endeavors.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
